      "order": 0,
      "text": "This energy is the sun’s energy stored up long ago by plants. Coal comes from the dead bodies of plants stored, away from the air and under pres- sure, through millions of years in great beds in the earth. The amount of coal and oil in the earth is, it is true, very great, but the amount we are using today is great too. A time may come before long when men will have used up all the coal and oil that is easy to get at.",
